The paper deals with pattern recognition and image classification tasks, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architectural similarity between ScatterNets and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular machine learning technique used in computer vision and other fields. Therefore, it is likely that the paper would also be relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT).
